========,1,preface.
Burton is a village in Geauga County, Ohio, United States.
The population was 1,455 at the 2010 census.
========,2,History.
Burton was founded in 1798 and is Geauga County's oldest settlement.
Like many other early settlements in the Connecticut Western Reserve, Burton has a town square patterned after the village greens of New England.
In 1972, an incident in Burton lead to a U.S. Supreme Court case.
Hugo Zacchini performed a human cannonball act at Burton's annual Geauga County Fair and WEWS-TV recorded and aired the entire act against his wishes and without compensating him, as was required by Ohio law.
In "Zacchini v. Scripps-Howard Broadcasting Co.", the high court ruled in 1977 that the First Amendment did not shield the broadcaster from liability from common law copyright claims.
========,2,Geography.
Burton is located at (41.471584, -81.146888).
